Uses of Interface
Chainable

    • Uses of Chainable in <Unnamed>

      Classes in <Unnamed> that implement Chainable 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  AdderFilter
      The AdderFilter adds points from its two inputs and produces a DataStream object containing the sums.
      class  DataStream
      The DataStream objects is an abstraction of an ArrayList of Double objects.
      class  Plotter
      The Plotter class is responsible for starting the flow of data from the bottom of the filter chain that will eventually be received by the Plotter object via its two inputs.
      class  ScalerFilter
      The ScalerFilter holds one Chainable input and performs the following operation on that input data: gain * x_i + base
